Global Biorational Crop Protection BCP Market Insights
Biorational Crop Protection BCP Market size was valued at USD 4.5 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 8.3 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 8.5% from 2024 to 2030.

Biorational Crop Protection BCP Market Overview
The global Biorational Crop Protection (BCP) market was valued at USD 8.2 billion in 2024 and is expected to grow at a CAGR of 9.1% during the forecast period from 2025 to 2032. BCP is gaining prominence due to the increasing demand for sustainable agricultural practices and a rising awareness about the environmental impact of chemical pesticides. The market's expansion is driven by innovations in biopesticides, integrated pest management (IPM), and the shift towards organic farming. North America and Europe are currently the leading markets, while Asia Pacific is expected to witness the fastest growth due to increased adoption of biorational products in emerging economies.

